Captain Siya Kolisi (C) celebrates and holds up the Web Ellis Trophy as the South African Rugby World Cup winner team parades on an open top bus.  CAPE TOWN - The Mother City is gearing up to welcome the Springboks on their final leg of the Rugby World Cup victory tour. The tour is expected to kick off at 10.30am at City Hall before continuing through the city centre. The Boks will then continue to visit Langa, Belhar, Elsies River and Ravensmead before returning to the city. The World Cup winners began their homecoming tour on Thursday with a victory parade in Pretoria, Johannesburg and Soweto.